      "text": "I argue that the fundamental problem with mortal harvesting is that it bestows more worth to the organs than to the one who has them insofar as it requires that a class of people (the donors) be judged to have lives that are less worthy of protections against killing than those of another class (the recipients).",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "3": {
      "text": "What is at stake, then, is the very basis of human equality, which, as I will also argue, should be based on an ineliminable dignity that each of us has in virtue of having a rational nature inherent to our human life form.",
